snippet.title: David Feinberg of Google Health @ 2020 StartUp Health Festival
snippet.description:
Vice President of Google Health, Dr. David Feinberg, talks with StartUp Health Chief Medial Officer, Howard Krein, MD, PhD, on the main stage of the StartUp Health Festival in San Francisco.  January 14, 2020.

Dr. David Feinberg has spent his entire career caring for people’s health and wellbeing. And after years in the healthcare system, he now leads Google Health, which brings together groups from across Google and Alphabet that are using AI, product expertise and hardware to take on big healthcare challenges.  (https://www.blog.google/technology/health/david-feinberg-google-health/)

Dr. Howard Krein is the Chief Medical Officer of StartUp Health, which was founded in 2011 to invest in a global army of entrepreneurs, called Health Transformers, committed to achieving health moonshots.

Dr. Krein is also an Assistant Professor of Otolaryngology: Head & Neck Surgery at Thomas Jefferson University and a founding partner and co-director of Jefferson’s Facial Aesthetic and Reconstructive Center. Additionally, he is the Senior Director of Health Policy & Innovation at the Sidney Kimmel Cancer Center. From 2017 to 2019, Dr. Krein served on the Biden Cancer Initiative’s Board of Directors.

Dr. Krein is part of an exclusive group of physicians with two doctorates, receiving his MD from Thomas Jefferson Medical College in Philadelphia and a PhD in Cell and Developmental Biology from UMDNJ/Robert Wood Johnson Medical School. Dr. Krein completed internships in both Emergency Medicine and General Surgery, a residency in Otolaryngology: Head and Neck Surgery at Thomas Jefferson University Hospital in Philadelphia and a Fellowship in Facial Plastic and Reconstructive Surgery at Medical College of Virginia in Richmond Virginia. He earned his Bachelor’s degree in Biology and a Master’s degree in Neuroscience from Rutgers University. Dr. Krein lives in Philadelphia, PA.

snippet.title: Loretta  | Google Super Bowl Commercial 2020
snippet.description:
A man reminisces about the love of his life with a little help from Google. 

See something in this story you want to try for yourself? Here are a few tips to get you started. 

First you’ll need the Google Assistant. If you don’t already have it, you can learn more at https://assistant.google.com

00:12 “Show me photos of me and Loretta” 
To use the Assistant to pull up photos, make sure you and your favorite people are tagged in your Google Photos. Then just say, “Hey Google, show me photos of me and [their name]” 

00:21 “Remember, Loretta hated my mustache.”
To try this one, just say, “Hey Google, remember…” and then whatever you’d like the Assistant to help you recall later. Like “Hey Google, remember Dad’s shoe size is 8 and half” or “remember Maria loves lilies.”  Then, to see everything you’ve asked the Assistant to remember, just say, “Hey Google, what did I tell you to remember?”

00:39 “Show me photos from our anniversary”
To see photos from a wedding, anniversary, birthday, or graduation, you’ll need a Google Photos account, and you’ll also need to tell your Assistant the specific date. Just say something like, “Hey Google, remember my anniversary is May 18th” or “remember Mark’s birthday is March 30th.” Then you can use that information in many ways, like “Hey Google, show me photos from our anniversary” or “Hey Google, remind me to buy flowers on Mark’s birthday.”

00:51 “Play our favorite movie.”
First, tell your Google Assistant what your favorite movie is by saying, “Hey Google, our favorite movie is Casablanca.” Once you’ve purchased your favorite movie on Google Play Movies or YouTube, all you have to say is, “Hey Google, play our favorite movie” and the movie will start playing.

snippet.title: Wildlife Insights: Saving Biodiversity with Tech and AI
snippet.description:
Biodiversity is in crisis. A recent UN report predicts we may see as many as 1 million species extincts, many as soon as within the decade. Wildlife Insights is a new Google Cloud -based platform that applies AI to identify animals in images from camera traps placed in the wild. AI helps reduce the arduous manual work of sifting through millions of camera trap images and helps biologists spend more time actually working to study and protect wildlife.

Watch the full-length documentary to learn how it’s being used in Colombia to measure the effects of deforestation on wildlife: https://youtu.be/zsiTx5qjn7c

snippet.title: How I’m making Maps better for wheelchair users like me
snippet.description:
Sasha Blair-Goldensohn is a Google employee who works on projects to help make Google Maps more accessible for everyone.

"Today, on International Day of Persons With Disabilities, I hope our work to make Google Maps more inclusive underscores what Angela Glover Blackwell wrote so powerfully about in “The Curb-Cut Effect.” When we build with accessibility in mind, it doesn’t just help people with disabilities. It helps everyone. Curb cuts in sidewalks don’t just help me cross the street—they also help parents pushing strollers, workers with deliveries and tourists with suitcases. As Blackwell puts it, building equity is not a zero-sum game—everyone benefits."

Learn more about Sasha by visiting https://goo.gle/35Z9SQS

snippet.title: Google Health - Tools to help healthcare providers deliver better care
snippet.description:
Health information is incredibly complex —there are misspellings, different ways of saying the same thing, handwritten scribbles, and faxes. Google has spent two decades on similar problems for consumers, building products such as Search, Translate and Gmail, and we believe we can adapt our technology to help. 

That’s why we’re building an intelligent suite of tools to help doctors, nurses, and other providers take better care of patients, leveraging our expertise in organizing information. One of those tools aims to make health records more useful, more accessible and more searchable by pulling them into a single, easy-to-use interface for doctors.

Learn more: https://health.google/clinicaltools/

snippet.title: Propel Bikes: Always moving forward
snippet.description:
After suffering a back injury while serving overseas in the U.S. Army Reserves, Chris Nolte turned to electric bikes as a way to return to his active lifestyle. Soon he was inspired to start his own electric bike company, with the hopes of transforming transportation and promoting sustainability. In 2011, he opened the business that would eventually become Propel Bikes in Brooklyn, New York, and in the years since, Chris has used digital tools from Google to find customers and grow his business. All that hard work is paying off--Chris recently opened a second location in Long Beach, California.  #GrowWithGoogle

Grow with Google offers free training and tools to help you grow your veteran-led business. Learn more at grow.google/veteranled

snippet.title: Strider Bikes: Inspiring riders worldwide
snippet.description:
As a bike enthusiast, Ryan McFarland couldn’t wait to share his love for riding with his two-year-old son. Instead of waiting for his son to grow old enough to use a traditional bike, Ryan invented a pedal-less bike that his toddler could ride immediately. He started Strider Bikes in 2007 and has since sold 2.5 million bikes worldwide, bringing joy to little riders in 78 countries. Today, international sales account for 60% of all Strider Bikes sold annually.

Since 2017, more than 3 million Americans have grown their businesses and careers with help from Grow with Google’s free training, tools and resources. Learn more about how small businesses are growing internationally at grow.google/export.  #GrowWithGoogle

snippet.title: Lifelines: How technology is transforming the world of emergency rescue
snippet.description:
Since the dawn of cell phones, first responders have struggled to locate many emergency callers who are unable to describe their locations. In 2016, a small team of Google engineers partnered with the European Emergency Number Association (EENA) to see how smartphone location technology might be able to help. 
 
This is a true story that followed—the tale of one paraglider in the lower Austrian Alps whose routine flight took a harrowing turn. 
 
Learn more about how technology is transforming the world of emergency rescue at  https://g.co/emergencylocation.
 
-------
 
Android Emergency Location Service (ELS) has been activated by more than 20 countries worldwide and helps first responders locate over 2M calls a day. To learn where ELS is available, review the FAQs here: https://crisisresponse.google/emergencylocationservice/faqs/.
 
If ELS works in your country and on your mobile network, then your phone will automatically send its location using ELS when you dial an emergency number. You can turn emergency location services on or off at any time. To learn more about how Android Emergency Location Service works and how to manage your Android device’s location settings, click here: https://support.google.com/android/answer/3467281?hl=en 
 
ELS performance may vary depending on environment, network conditions, partner choice of transmission protocol and confidence level.

------

Director: Nick Carbonaro
Cinematographer: Karl Erik Brøndbo
Editor: Kyle Valenta

snippet.title: Robbie's Voice-Activated Room
snippet.description: Robbie has duchenne muscular dystrophy, which has left him able to control only his eyes, head and right thumb joint. Among the many challenges Robbie and his family face are his bedtime routine. For years, Robbie’s mom Carrie has set her alarm every few hours to get up and change his position in bed so he doesn’t get bed sores. Earlier this year, a sleep-deprived Carrie put out a message to the Muscular Dystrophy Association asking for help to try and find a better way. She got a response from Bill Weis, a retired tech worker, who thought he could set up Robbie’s bed to be controlled by voice activation. While working on the bed, Bill had an epiphany: if he can control the bed this way, why not everything else in Robbie’s bedroom universe?

snippet.title: How Merkle is championing #IamRemarkable for their employees globally
snippet.description:
The #IamRemarkable initiative from Google, empowers women and underrepresented groups to speak openly about their accomplishments and improve their self-promotion skills. 
After attending an #IamRemarkable workshop, Egle Mazonaite was inspired to bring #IamRemarkable to her Merkle colleagues. During International Women's Day 2019 Merkle employees ran over 40 workshops to more than 600 employees across the US. As a result, the company saw better performance, team cohesion and inclusion - so much so that they are now rolling the workshops out globally.
The #IamRemarkable initiative was founded by Anna Vainer in 2015. Anna is a Product Marketing Manager at Google, working from London on B2B growth marketing across EMEA.
The #IamRemarkable movement has reached over 50,000 participants across 62 countries as of July 2019. 
Learn more, and sign up for free to become a facilitator at g.co/iamremarkable

snippet.title: Any student can be inspired by the possibilities of computer science
snippet.description:
Google and 4-H, the nation’s largest youth development organization, are working together to provide young Americans the opportunity to learn computer science through hands-on activities in their own communities. 

West Virginia native, Decklan Thomas, doesn’t consider himself a programming whiz, but access to these resources have expanded his perspective. Learning how to code helps kids develop the analytical, creative, and critical thinking necessary to be creators and problem-solvers in any field.  

Google.org is granting $6 million to 4-H, in a follow up to a $1.5 million grant in 2017. Over the next three years, the program will reach more than one million 4-H youth across America – 60% who live in rural communities. 

Read more about this initiative here: goo.gle/2WCP2lw

snippet.title: YouTube Creators for Change: Omar Hussein
snippet.description:
Omar Hussein is a creator who found his voice on YouTube. Omar created "Al-Tayer" a social satire show focused on the Saudi environment surrounding him. As his show gained popularity, Omar became the CEO of Uturn Entertainment, a leading multi-channel network in Saudi Arabia. As his channel neared a million subscribers, Omar stopped broadcasting his show and focused on earning a master’s degree in the UK. Omar has diversified his interest in YouTube by creating a new, self-titled vlogging channel which has become his primary home on the site.

For his YouTube Creators for Change project, Omar aims to promote empathy and understanding towards the Muslim community through a music video that demonstrates the importance of education as a way to generate tolerance and acceptance for everyone.

To see Omar's Creators for Change project, visit his channel -- https://www.youtube.com/user/honga1st

snippet.title: #VeteransDay: Thank You for Everything
snippet.description:
This #VeteransDay, we want to say thank you to those who’ve served their country and shared their stories with the world.

Today and every day, we at YouTube salute everything you have done and continue to do -- for your families, for communities, and for our nation.

snippet.title: YouTube Creators for Change: Franchesca Ramsey
snippet.description:
Franchesca Ramsey is a YouTube vlogger and writer known for her unique voice, social commentary and comedy. In 2016, Franchesca was one of four YouTube creators who asked live video questions of the US presidential candidates at the Democratic debates in Charleston, South Carolina. In addition to making YouTube videos, she's a former writer and correspondent for Comedy Central's ""The Nightly Show with Larry Wilmore"" and is currently the host of MTV's ""Decoded"".

For her YouTube Creators for Change project, Franchesca discusses policing in America today and presents some impactful ways to use your voice in your local community.

To see Franchesca's Creators for Change project, visit her channel -- https://www.youtube.com/user/chescaleigh

snippet.title: YouTube Creators for Change: Dina Tokio
snippet.description:
London-based blogger and recent mom Dina Tokio has a keen eye for fashion and all things beauty related. She creates content for her YouTube channel and blog that ranges from styling tips to everyday lifestyle vlogs and passionate rants. Dina was part of YouTube's #MadeForYou campaign, where she was selected as one the UK's most influential social media stars of the moment!

For her YouTube Creators for Change project, Dina has created a four-part series that aims to celebrate Muslim women who have shunned cultural stereotypes in hopes of inspiring young girls that they can go on to do whatever it is they want in life with or without a hijab.


To see Dina's Creators for Change project, visit her channel -- https://www.youtube.com/user/dinatokio

snippet.title: YouTube TV + Julio Jones: All The Julios
snippet.description:
Introducing YouTube TV.
Finally, cable-free live TV. Try it free here: https://tv.youtube.com

YouTube TV is a TV streaming service that lets you watch live TV from ABC, CBS, FOX, NBC, and popular cable networks. Enjoy local and national live sports, and must-see shows the moment they air. Record all your favorites without DVR storage space limits, and stream wherever you go. YouTube TV comes with 6 accounts per household.

YouTube TV is currently available in select U.S. cities, with more coming soon! Learn where we’re launched here: https://tv.youtube.com/tv/availability.

snippet.title: YouTube Creators for Change: Natalie Tran
snippet.description:
Since uploading her first video on YouTube in 2006, Natalie Tran’s YouTube channel has grown a global fanbase of over 1.8 million subscribers with over half a billion channel views. Tran's videos are a collection of scripted comedy clips that contain a mixture of monologues and sketches focusing on the oddities of awkward everyday situations – with Tran playing multiple characters.

For her YouTube Creators for Change project, Natalie created a short series of videos from her very personal experiences that tackle some of the racism and sexism people in interracial relationships face in hopes of generating understanding and empathy.

To see Natalie's Creators for Change project, visit her channel -- https://www.youtube.com/user/communitychannel

snippet.title: YouTube Creators for Change: Abdel En Vrai
snippet.description:
Abdel discovered his passion for making people laugh through stand-up comedy. He started his YouTube channel, Abdel en Vrai, 3 years ago and uses it to share content about peace, love and tolerance. Humor helps get the message across with more impact. Abdel has always been an activist for equality and social justice, which led him to win the Brussels Citizen of the Year Award in 2013.

For his YouTube Creators for Change project, Abdel hosted two workshop-style events focused on engaging Belgian youth with content creation. Additionally, he will be releasing a series of videos to further his message about Muslim tolerance and acceptance.

To view Abdel's Creators for Change project, visit his channel -- https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCfQKQmVsZVslQsVhK_eR-mw

snippet.title: YouTube Creators for Change: Barış Özcan
snippet.description:
Istanbul-based storyteller Baris produces and broadcasts YouTube videos about art, design, technology and literature. Every week, Baris tries to tell simple stories around complex technological concepts and social issues. Baris is an award-winning art director at Abak.us – the creative agency he founded – and a prominent public speaker at events like TEDx in Turkey. He is married to one of the first-ever Turkish internet bloggers, Devletsah, and has a son.

For his YouTube Creators for Change project, Baris produced a six-part YouTube series in scripted/fiction format on topics related to hate, race, religion, sexual orientation, extremism and xenophobia. Each webisode will bring us into the world of a detective furiously working solve to a mystery and show us his experiences with some of the darkest corners of human nature.

To see Baris' Creators for Change project, visit his channel channel -- https://www.youtube.com/user/b31416

snippet.title: YouTube: What will you watch next?
snippet.description: YouTube has an updated look and new features. With a simplified design that lets content shine and new ways to watch like dark theme and adjustable speed playback on mobile, the redesigned experience now looks cleaner and more consistent across both desktop and mobile devices.

snippet.title: YouTube Creators for Change: AIB
snippet.description:
All India Bakchod (AIB) is one of India's funniest and edgiest comedy collectives. Consisting of comedians Rohan Joshi, Tanmay Bhat, Gursimran Khamba and Ashish Shakya, AIB has revolutionized comedy content in India. They started with India’s first ever, and most heard, comedy podcast, then went on to become one of the biggest YouTube channels in India with over 1.7 million subscribers. In 2015, they did the first ever news comedy show "On Air With AIB" which was seen on digital as well as prime time television. AIB belongs to an emerging group of digital crusaders advocating for the cause of net neutrality in India.

For their YouTube Creators for Change project, they use comedic parody to highlight the harassment, misogyny and hatred women face online every day and create a conversation around how to make digital environments safer.

To see AIB's Creators for Change project, visit their channel: https://www.youtube.com/user/allindiabakchod

snippet.title: YouTube Creators for Change: Cameo Project
snippet.description:
Cameo Project is a YouTube channel based in Indonesia. They are known for their fun, lively videos in which they talk about social issues and sensitive topics in Indonesia in order to raise awareness among the Indonesian people. In addition to videos centered around politics and social issues, they make funny, relatable videos about life in Indonesia.

For their YouTube Creators for Change project, Cameo partnered with an NGO called ""Maarif Institute"" who has a wide network of students across the country. Together they aim to educate high school and university students in 10 cities in Indonesia about the importance of creating positive content.

snippet.title: #ProudToBe: Celebrate Brave Voices this Pride
snippet.description:
In a world where some people still try to silence LGBTQ+ voices, the act of being yourself is an act of bravery for all to see. And in the context of a global climate that highlights the vulnerability of LGBTQ+ rights, it’s more important than ever that LGBTQ+ voices and stories are shared and heard. 

An inclusive, vibrant, ever-expanding LGBTQ+ community has been a vital part of YouTube since we started. And we’re proud to stand with a group that believes every human being deserves the right to be who they are and love who they love. So to all those brave voices who continue to make Youtube the colorful, diverse and supportive place it is, we’re #ProudToBe with you.

--

YouTube Creators for Change is proud to launch #ProudToBe, our fifth annual Pride campaign. Creators for Change is YouTube’s global initiative dedicated to amplifying the voices of role models who are tackling difficult social issues with their channels. From combating hate speech, to countering xenophobia and extremism, to simply making the case for greater tolerance and empathy toward others, these creators are helping generate positive social change with their global fan bases. Learn more at https://www.youtube.com/yt/creators-for-change/

snippet.title: YouTube: Our Brand Mission
snippet.description:
Our mission is to give everyone a voice and show them the world.
We believe that everyone deserves to have a voice, and that the world is a better place when we listen, share and build community through our stories. Our values are based on four essential freedoms that define who we are: freedom of expression, freedom of opportunity, freedom of information and the freedom to belong

For more about who we are visit www.youtube.com/yt/about

snippet.title: #ProudToBe: Coming Together to Celebrate Identity
snippet.description:
Celebrating the inspiring voices who are #ProudToBe
SHARE THIS VIDEO: https://youtu.be/dtCyepuLt8Q
MUSIC: "Nothing Without Love" by Nate Ruess

From commemorating Pride parades to opening up about transitions and explaining the ABCs of LGBT (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uFqLrSHWNT4), YouTube is a place where anyone can belong no matter who they are or who they love. That is why today we want to help people honor and celebrate who they’re #ProudToBe.

Now, more than ever, it’s important that we help accept, love, and celebrate one another. In the wake of the tragic events in Orlando, we stand together in support of the LGBTQ community. We stand together with everyone who has the courage to own and share their identity. We stand together to show the power of solidarity, the power of love, the power of pride. To those beautiful and brave voices who continue to make YouTube the vibrant, diverse and empathetic community it is, we are #ProudToBe with you.

JOIN IN: Who are you #ProudToBe? 
Upload a video or share a post with #ProudToBe in the title so others can find it.

snippet.title: Highlights From the YouTube Interview with President Obama
snippet.description: On Jan 15, 2016, President Obama sat down for an interview after his final State of the Union with three popular YouTube creators, Adande Thorne, Destin Sandlin, and Ingrid Nilsen. snippet.title: Announcing the YouTube Interview With President Obama
snippet.description:

This Friday, three top YouTube creators -- Destin Sandlin, Ingrid Nilsen, Adande Thorne -- will interview President Obama, after his final State of the Union, directly from the East Room of the White House. They will ask the president questions that are top of mind for them and their fans, tackling issues big and small, poignant and personal.

snippet.title: #ProudToLove - Celebrating Marriage Equality and LGBT Pride Month
snippet.description:
YouTube is #ProudToLove the LGBT community and marriage equality. 
SHARE THIS VIDEO: https://youtu.be/WSiehK2asbI

Over the last 10 years, everyone from moms to presidents have uploaded videos in support of LGBT awareness, to stand up against bullying and discrimination, and to say together, as a community, that marriage equality matters.

snippet.title: Welcome to the School of YouTube: #LaughLearnGive
snippet.description:
To donate to Comic Relief, click here:
http://comicrelief.com/SOYT

If you’re in the U.K., text SOYT to 70005. Texts cost £5 plus your standard network message charge. £5 per text goes to Comic Relief. You must be 16 or over and please ask the bill : payer’s permission. For full terms and conditions and more information go to www.comicrelief.com/terms-of-use
 
If you’re in the U.S., text  SOYT to 71777 to make a pledge. Then just click the link you get back to fill in your credit card information. Message and data rates may apply.

Join our headmaster for a tour around a school like no other, as this week we laugh, learn, and give at the School of YouTube. 

This week your favourite creators will be learning something new, teaching skills you never knew they had, pushing themselves like never before - or simply embarrassing themselves in public. 

Why? Because, while millions around the world will be going back to school this month, many children in areas of extreme poverty, or conflict, simply don’t have access to a quality education.

So this week, if you learn a little, or laugh a little, consider giving a little, to help those less fortunate go to school. Money raised will go to Comic Relief UK

#laughlearngive
See what those creators have been up to at youtube.com/youtube.

snippet.title: Gay Gaming

snippet.description: From autonomous autos to motorcycle/car hybrids to hands-free driving to an electric superbike that breaks the 100 mph barrier, the future of transportation could hit the roads as early as next year.

snippet.title: Iraq Crisis: Explained
snippet.description: These videos explain the complex political and cultural crisis in Iraq, the roles that ISIS, Syria, Iran, and the U.S. play in it, and how the situation could have implications across the Middle East.

snippet.title: Spotlight On: Sam Smith
snippet.description: From his chart-topping collaborations with Disclosure and Naughty Boy to his breakout solo LP, "In the Lonely Hour," get up close and personal with the 2014 BRIT Critics' Choice Award winner, Sam Smith.

snippet.title: World Cup: Fans React Worldwide
snippet.description: Many countries have experienced both the thrill of victory and the agony of defeat, as demonstrated by fútbol fans planet-wide celebrating the World Cup's most breathtaking moments.

snippet.title: BBQ Science
snippet.description: Chemical reactions, thermodynamics, physics, and condiments: there's more to great BBQ than mere meat and heat. Here's some of the science behind your next summertime spread.

snippet.title: Expectations vs. Reality
snippet.description: Some things seem too good to be true, and are frequently just that. As these videos reveal, reality doesn't always meet our expectations.

snippet.title: 10 Most Creative Music Videos of 2014 (So Far...)
snippet.description: These music videos substitute ingenuity and creative visual concepts for big-budget glitz, and they'll be stuck in your head long after you've forgotten the tune.

snippet.title: We Heart Old Tech
snippet.description: These devices might be obsolete, but they're still so neat. Take a nostalgic look at the cutting edge technology of yesteryear.

snippet.title: Dreams Do Come True
snippet.description: Guaranteed to provoke reflection and warm your heart, these videos show people from all walks of life gathering together to bring a young child's dream to fruition.

snippet.title: Spotlight On: Dave Chappelle
snippet.description: One of the most successful comedy shows in cable history? Check. Mysterious hiatus? Check. Re-emerging stand-up act? Check. A decade after stepping out, the comedy mastermind returns to the spotlight.

snippet.title: 'Transformers' Fans Transform
snippet.description: Celebrate the release of "Transformers: Age of Extinction," the latest installment in the mega-smash franchise, with these fan-driven odes to the robots in disguise.

snippet.title: Trending: World Cup Re-Creations
snippet.description: Using Legos, animations, and flip books, these creators re-enact some of the most famous moments in World Cup history, from the "Hand of God" to this year's most surprising goals.

snippet.title: Damn, Nature: You Scary
snippet.description: Get up close and very personal with some of Mother Nature's creatures that you might not want to meet in person--including a scorpion, a puff adder, a very hungry jaguar, and more.

snippet.title: The Internet in Numbers
snippet.description: How much does the Internet weigh, are we really all separated by only six people, how "deep" is the Deep Web, and how much is a "like" worth? Prepare for brain expansion.

snippet.title: You Eat That!?
snippet.description: We are what we eat ... but just what exactly are we eating? From sugar to gluten to wood pulp and lanolin (!), get to know the ingredients in your food and the truth behind your diet.

snippet.title: Believe in Bees
snippet.description: Get the buzz on one of nature's foremost pollinators and learn why those black and yellow friends really are the bee's knees. And even if you once had doubts, these videos will make you a bee-liever.

snippet.title: Trending: YouTube Heartthrobs
snippet.description: They're young, attractive, engaging, and are now headlining at shows and festivals around the country. They all got their start--and their fans--with simple vlogs and creative videos.

snippet.title: Kitchen Remixes
snippet.description: Introducing kitchen-step. Chefs-turned-musicians create original tunes with bottles, pans, salt shakers, and just about every other cooking item imaginable, including the kitchen sink.

snippet.title: Magnificent 'Maleficent' Fans
snippet.description: Maleficent might not be the most iconic or noteworthy Disney villain, but Angelina Jolie's portrayal in the movie has caused quite the whirlwind of covers, makeup tutorials, and comedic send-ups.

snippet.title: The 'TFIOS' Phenomenon
snippet.description: Did you know "The Fault in Our Stars" was the brainchild of Vlogbrother John Green? Here's how both the book and movie came to be, and how fans have embraced the story--and awesomeness--since Day 1.

snippet.title: June 21 - 10 Ways to Enjoy the Summer Solstice
snippet.description: The present's so bright, you have to wear shades, and today you'll have to wear them longer than any other day. Here are 10 creative, extreme, and downright crazy ways to celebrate 2014's summer solstice.

snippet.description: Cyborgs at the World Cup, the Internet's new private investigators, how many people an NBA player is worth (salary-wise), why we have seasons, and boosting creativity round out this Week in Ideas.

snippet.title: Sloth Power!
snippet.description: Cats? Too snobby. Dogs? Too slobby. Sloths? Perfect. They're weird, adorable, and chill to the max. Now they're challenging, slooowwwly, the Internet's cutest animals for meme hegemony.

snippet.title: Spotlight On: LeVar Burton
snippet.description: Meet the icon behind Geordi La Forge of "Star Trek: The Next Generation," Kunta Kinte from "Roots," and the former host of the much-beloved "Reading Rainbow."

snippet.title: It Only Takes an Hour
snippet.description: Join the Made with Code movement to celebrate the women who've used coding to create toys, apps, and video games. Together, these leaders pave the way for more women to storm the tech industry and change the world.

snippet.title: DIY Checkup
snippet.description: Feelin' odd? Or just want to know how your bod works? These videos have a lot of information to help you help yourself, and check if you need to see a real M.D.

snippet.title: Famous Cats: Where Are They Now?
snippet.description: From Nyan Cat to Lil Bub, from Colonel Meow to Grumpy Cat and beyond, go behind the purr and get an updated look at the Internet's most famous felines.

snippet.title: 10 Epic Trick Shot Videos
snippet.description: No camera tricks, slick editing, or CGI here: just pure skill. Trick shot experts manipulate soccer balls, frisbees, bowling balls, basketballs, and more in jaw-droppingly unbelievable ways.

snippet.title: Surprising Street Concerts
snippet.description: These impromptu performers prove that all the world's a stage. They take to the street, grocery store, train, and even an airport tarmac to unleash their talents.

snippet.description: How do your ears work? These videos explain all sorts of auditory phenomena, including aural illusions, holophonic sounds, and the strange reason we dislike the sound of our own voice.

snippet.description: Tossing out that ceremonial first pitch is a pressure-packed moment: a fan-filled stadium, a menacing mound, and a throw that looks easy on TV but is w-a-a-a-y longer--60.5 feet, actually--in real life.

snippet.title: Tyler Farr - Dear Tyler
snippet.description:
Dear Tyler Farr

Missouri-born Tyler Farr has as boomin' baritone voice that really knows how to put its scratchy side to good use, and when he applies it to twang-driven songs like "Hot Mess" and "A Guy Walks Into a Bar," you can feel the passion pouring out. Maybe that's because he had some classical vocal training early on, or maybe it's because the country hit-maker, who keeps the charts poppin' with smashes such as "Redneck Crazy" and "Whiskey In My Water," really takes a lyric to heart when he cuts a song. It's been a couple years since his 'Suffer In Peace' album, and to celebrate the arrival of his new track "I Should Got To Church Sometime," we connected with him at CMA Festival in Nashville for a little fun. The guy who once did an interview show with questions asked by kids agreed to dispense all sorts of practical wisdom in our new various-artists advice series. 'Dear Tyler Farr' finds him helping fans with problems like curing a hangover, accidentally shooting a pal's tire on a hunting trip, and telling your dad you're ditching college for a music career. He doesn't hold back on any of the answers. See what he has to say in 'Dear Tyler Farr.'

Americana was written, conceived, and arranged, by Davies, and co-produced with Guy Massey and John Jackson. snippet.title: Didirri - Raw Stuff [Official Music Video]
snippet.description:
For the first time in my life, I was skipping Christmas. I was feeling very, very guilty about it... Raw Stuff instantly fell into two parts. The first half is my side of miscommunication, and the second my reaction to hearing they felt the same.

Songwriting really helps me express things that I may otherwise be without words to explain. ‘Raw stuff’ is one of those songs that just stood out when I was writing. Sometimes a song just speaks to me more than others. 

I wrote this song as a dedication to a dear person in my life. In performance, ‘Raw stuff’ cuts close to the bone for me. It’s a difficult song to sing, both emotionally taxing and physically. It is a moment for reflection. 

I find now, I'm sharing this song for anyone else who is trying to process what’s happening in their life. 

Didirri x

from my old neighborhood.

in each of my cells.

he calls me all the time.

I just walked away,

Look what I've become.

Rollin’ through South Central, better watch your ass.
Bars all on my windows,
Pistol on my bed stand.
To live and die in L.A.

Murder, murder, murder, Lord mercy me.

Directed by Toby Pike

LYRICS

Yeah.
I can worry, I can overthink things.
That's exactly when I tend to want to drink things.
Tend to wanna smoke things ‘til I realized there's no thing outside of me.
That kinda helped me grow wings.
Listen up. I think this is dope:
To love is very different than to own.
Let that sink in.

I grew my hair but never lost my J Dilla vibe.
Airplane mode: don't kill the vibe.
I had to remind people I was still alive.
I had to remind people of what's real inside.
Yeah, yeah I'm the 'I Took a Pill in' guy.
But even more beautiful with no pill inside.
Feel the vibe?

I wanted to be Deion. I was more Wojciechowski.
My friends gon' hit the club, I tell 'em go without me.
There's a lot that these people don't know about me.
I've always been that dude though, no Lebowski (haha stupid).
Old friends never tell me that I seem different.
Ashamed of the way that I used to treat women.
Objectified.
Embarrassed but I'll never lie.
Mac is dead; many more are dead inside.
Hideous thoughts in this head of mine.
I'll choose different ones.
Life hit me in the face but I didn't run.
Perhaps Michigan will be the place my kids are from.
Ram Dass is the man I got the vision from.

It's alright (yeah).
It's alright (yeah).
Uh, ay.

I donated all my Jordans.
Didn't do a post, they were taking up the space that I needed to grow.
That was a Sage Francis line; I stole it,
But there was no better way to say that
There is no future, no time.
Look at yourself; don't be so bovine.
Courage used to be something that I couldn't find.
People scared to look at their dreams so they look at mine (yeah).
Whatever makes you feel good inside.
It's alright.

I was in the gym the other day in Los Angeles.
And I saw all of the beautiful bodies
Running on the treadmills, staring at the screens.
And it reminded me of hamsters running on the wheel.
And that's when I really decided right then and there
I'm not going to be a hamster on a wheel.
I'm gon' do it.
Twitter is apoplectic,
Squirrels with acorns.
I said it before:
Ships are safe in the harbor, but that ain't what ships are made for.
I say I am not my haircut, I'm not my body,
Not my clothes; I'm something much more beautiful,
Deeper than even I know.
Took me thirty years to wake up and write this song.
Took me thirty years to realize nothing is wrong.

snippet.title: Gary West - Jackson ft. Leona Williams
snippet.description:
On January 22, 2019, Gary West and Leona Williams meet in person for the first time at a Nashville recording studio. At 1pm that day, a friendship was forged. Although they had spoken on the phone and had exchanged several text messages, Gary admits it was difficult to sleep the night before as nerves set in.

Leona Williams is regarded as one of the most revered lady singer/songwriters in all of country music. Leona Williams was married to Merle Haggard from 1978 and 1983. She wrote two #1 hits for him, "Someday When Things Are Good" and "You Take Me For Granted". She wrote songs for Connie Smith and Loretta Lynn and more. She also charted 8 times on Hot Country Songs with a duet with Haggard titled "The Bull and the Beaver" peaking at #8 of the Country Top 40 hits.

"JACKSON", is a song written in 1963 by Billy Edd Wheeler and Jerry Leiber and was first recorded by Wheeler. Johnny Cash and June Carter recorded "Jackson" in 1967.

Gary West and Leona Williams brand their own firey "folk-a-billy" style version of Jackson, produced by Gary West and featuring his amazing, legendary Nashville band.

http://vevo.ly/TG09qJ

Behind the handsome face, tattoo sleeves, a marriage to fellow country star Carly Pearce and his own flourishing career, Michael Ray wants you to know its ok to be vulnerable. Divorce shattered Ray’s childhood when he was eight, leading him to lean heavily on his grandparents. Ray’s grandfather taught his grandson how to play music and would bring the future country star to perform at local assisted living homes. Ray won’t let himself forget his grandparents’ love and sacrifice. He named his 2018 album, Amos, after his grandpa; For tour, he outfitted his drummer’s bass drum head to resemble a bronze penny - a reference to his grandmother’s nickname, Penny. Nowadays, Ray is outspoken about his anxiety - and his personal battles confronting it head on. We invited the Nashville resident to the studio, where he performed “Forget About It” and “Her World Or Mine.” In both songs, Ray invites listeners to connect with those moments of self-doubt, and, as he says in the Behind the Song for “Her World Or Mine,” “allow yourself to feel it and then move forward.”

snippet.title: Tainy - The Kid Who Grew Up On Reggaeton | Vevo
snippet.description:
Tainy - Kid Who Grew Up On Reggaeton

Marco Masís, más conocido como Tainy, es uno de los productores de reggaeton más reconocidos del mundo. Por más de 10 años Tainy ha estado detrás de la explosión del género a nivel mundial. Colaborando con OG’s como Wisin & Yandel y con la nueva ola de superestrellas como J Balvin y Bad Bunny, Tainy ha colaborado con los más renombrados del reggaeton. Nuestro crew siguió a Tainy en Miami. Filmando en locaciones como Jose Marti basketball courts y NEON16 Studio, Tainy nos relata en primera persona la importancia de lo que se viene en su música. Y por supuesto, el soundtrack del vídeo es un Tainy Original.

Marco Masís is the reggaeton super-producer known as Tainy. For more than a decade, the Puerto Rican hit maker has led the charge of reggaeton’s worldwide takeover. From OGs like Wisin & Yandel to the new school pop stars like J Balvin and Bad Bunny, Tainy has collaborated with the best of the best. Our crew caught up with him in Miami. We filmed him while he hooped with friends at Jose Marti park and kicked it at his studio, NEON16. And, of course, that beat you hear is a Tainy original.

snippet.title: Jhay Cortez - Subiendo De Nivel (Live Session) | Vevo Ctrl
snippet.description:
Jhay Cortez - Sobiendo De Nivel (Vevo Ctrl)

You know the talent is deep when elders want to work with a newcomer. Jhay Cortez has been thinking about how he wanted his music to sounds for years now, ever since he was a kid, really. When he hit the professional scene in 2018, the reaction was instantaneous. The Puerto Rican upstart's blend of reggaeton and trap-pop had established stars signing up for feature and giving shout-outs galore. J Balvin, Bad Bunny, Greeicy, Karol G, Ozuna, Sky, Wisin y Yandel - the list goes on and on. Last summer's 'Famouz' was pure fire and the recent "reloaded" version of the project throws more jewels at the fans. We had our DSCVR alum in for a Ctrl session, and he scalded the place. Watch "Subiendo De Nivel" and "Tocarte" to get a taste of what put him on top so quickly. 

Watch Jhay Cortez videos: https://bit.ly/30DHxha

snippet.title: Aesop Rock - Rogue Wave (Official Video)
snippet.description:
LISTEN TO ROGUE WAVE: https://rse.lnk.to/RogueWave
BUY ROGUE WAVE VINYL + MERCH: http://bit.ly/RogueWaveFE
SUBSCRIBE FOR MORE: http://bit.ly/RhymesayersYT

MORE ON AESOP ROCK:
https://rhymesayers.com/aesoprock
https://facebook.com/aesoprockwins
https://twitter.com/aesoprockwins
https://instagram.com/aesoprockwins

LYRICS:
A little bread, a little circus, it serve as a diversion for devils and death merchants, I was curled up underneath the swirling threat of reds and purples, lumberjack flannel, strapping saddles over servals, paddling in circles with 10,000 maniacs in yankee caps, who get to know the neighbors every time they tip the ladle back, rag tag cats and canines who catch phat tags on the fabric of space time, all work no play, dull boys rotate, Old Boy, Ghostface, Tolstoy, Coltrane, throws up coffin nails, off the rails, born bathed in a tornado of claws and tails, got skulls on his sails, cobras on the pleather, salt and pepper soldiers barely holding it together, but supposedly awoke and down to mobilize whenever, you’re pretty much a Gomer Pyle to pester, remember, I’m Pop-O-Matic trouble, I will commander the goulash under hockey hair, zoom off on a blue ox through the blogosphere with poppies for your mama bear, carrots for the vitamix, kibble for the puppy, something bloody for the firebit, never mind the appetizer writhing in the spider web, stare into it long enough you biters just might find yourselves, tea with the dark side, Slimer on speed dial, sleep on a couch or a street or a leaf pile, our kind can not be redeemed, I’m a cancer on the glamor, I can’t with the “Me Me Me”, no anesthesia, surgeon with the signal jammer scrambling the feed, distributing the panacea free, all day, there is no amount of Our Fathers that could remedy the black dog breathing down his collar, mi casa like I’m Oscar, hot and popping out a flipped lid, eyepatch, Prince wig, disappearing grid blip, stiff lip, sure to shit talk a centurion, tsk tsk, I don’t really wiggle with invertebrates, purp in the thurible, off sides, toss thine merch in the urinal, it’s nothing personal, dirtbag don, don’t provoke him to act up, I’m golden doing donuts in the Totoro cat bus, everything I touch turn to black sludge, bugs in the bag lunch, punch through a mack truck, hunchback, get y’all acquainted with the contagion, nobody safe, say hello to well beyond containment, I came for every cell between the belfry and the basement, you maybe wanna telephone your favorites, we take it where the warlocks lock horns, soda pop, popcorn, top notch gore set to Bach over fog horns, snotty nose, clogged pores, fork in his heart, back away or catch a halo made of orbiting stars, yea, transform in the dark, got a dog nose sniffing out the source of the snark, got a cat’s ears twitching every snap of a twig, triangulate your position, a simple rabbit to skin, I been an echo in the dark who demo applied science at the parlay, barf rainbows and cry diamonds, ok, ready Freddy, headlong into creeping death, respawn where you least expect, I could pick a pin and tumbler right in front of the guard, out the front with another Picasso under his arm, hit the city limit still exhibiting his inner Caulfield, baby, I’m H.E. double hockey sticks on wheels, new dawn, show ‘em how the voodoo feels, plus launch fireballs from the palm heels, on an otherwise slow day, this is how I row into the rogue wave, yo...

VIDEO CREDITS:
Directed by Rob Shaw
Illustrations by Aesop Rock

SONG CREDITS:
Written and Produced by Aesop Rock
Guitar by James Lynch

#RogueWave #AesopRock #Rhymesayers
